        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 6:35PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 634 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Hartwell, or near Bowman. This storm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Royston and Vanna.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
